+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01V6mPgfyrfkj9DfaVUTFQi2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good, dependencies are installed. Now let me design my approach.\n\n## Design\n\n**`simulate`**: Topological processing - keep trying to evaluate gates whose inputs are available until all gates fire. Simple iterative approach.\n\n**`findSwappedWires`**: Structural analysis of the ripple-carry adder pattern. For each bit position, verify the expected gate structure:\n- Bit 0: `x00 XOR y00 -> z00`, `x00 AND y00 -> carry`\n- Bit N (N>0): `xN XOR yN -> tN` (partial sum XOR), `tN XOR carry_prev -> zN` (sum), `xN AND yN -> aN` (generate), `tN AND carry_prev -> bN` (propagate), `aN OR bN -> cN` (carry out)\n- Final bit: last carry -> z(N+1)\n\nThe key insight: check each gate's role against what a correct adder would produce, identify structural violations, and find the 4 swapped pairs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":20656,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b652f3a-f921-4a07-9246-2ee54cf992bd","uuid":"5230e16e-9ce5-43cd-a470-01dafd207403"}
