+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EsZAkGSjmoGp6oBGorxHSk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015ENHaF18Bf6Ebqqm7mUq54","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"OUTPUT=$(gemini -p 'Implement a circuit simulator and wire-swap debugger in TypeScript at src/index.ts.\n\nThe file must export two functions and a Gate interface.\n\nRequirements:\n\n1. Export this interface:\n```typescript\ninterface Gate {\n  op: \"AND\" | \"OR\" | \"XOR\";\n  in1: string;\n  in2: string;\n  out: string;\n}\n```\n\n2. Export function `simulate(gates: Gate[], inputs: Record<string, number>): Record<string, number>`:\n   - Takes gates and initial wire values (0 or 1)\n   - Simulates the circuit by processing gates in dependency order\n   - A gate fires when both its inputs have known values\n   - AND: output is 1 only if both inputs are 1\n   - OR: output is 1 if at least one input is 1\n   - XOR: output is 1 if exactly one input is 1\n   - Returns final value of every wire (inputs + computed)\n   - Implementation: iteratively scan all gates, fire those with both inputs ready, repeat until all gates have fired\n\n3. Export function `findSwappedWires(gates: Gate[]): string[]`:\n   - The gates describe a ripple-carry binary adder for X+Y=Z\n   - Input wires: x00..xNN, y00..yNN; output wires: z00..z(NN+1)\n   - Exactly 4 pairs of gate output wires have been swapped (8 wires total)\n   - Must return sorted array of the 8 swapped wire names\n   - Must handle up to 45 input bits (~220 gates) in under 5 seconds\n   - Brute force is NOT feasible\n\n   Algorithm for findSwappedWires - structural analysis approach:\n   \n   The correct adder pattern for each bit position is:\n   - Bit 0: xor_gate(x00, y00) -> z00; and_gate(x00, y00) -> carry[0]\n   - Bit N (N>0): \n     * xor1 = xor_gate(xN, yN) -> partial_sum  (the \"t\" wire)\n     * xor2 = xor_gate(partial_sum, carry[N-1]) -> zN  (final sum)\n     * and1 = and_gate(xN, yN) -> generate  (the \"a\" wire)\n     * and2 = and_gate(partial_sum, carry[N-1]) -> propagate (the \"b\" wire)\n     * or1 = or_gate(generate, propagate) -> carry[N]\n   - Final: carry[last] -> z(NN+1)\n\n   Implementation strategy:\n   a. Build lookup maps: by output wire, and by (op, inputs) -> gate\n   b. Walk bit by bit from bit 0 to the highest bit\n   c. For each bit, find the gates that should form the adder structure\n   d. When a gate output does not match the expected pattern (e.g., a XOR of xN and yN should NOT output to a z wire for N>0, or a second XOR should output to zN), flag it as swapped\n   e. Track the carry wire through each bit position\n   f. Collect all swapped wires and return sorted\n\n   More specifically, use these rules to detect swaps:\n   - For bit 0: Find the XOR gate with inputs x00,y00. Its output should be z00. Find the AND gate with inputs x00,y00. Its output is the carry.\n   - For bit N>0: Find the XOR gate with inputs xN,yN. Call its output wire W. \n     * If W starts with \"z\" (and is not the last z bit), W is swapped - it should be an intermediate wire.\n     * Find the XOR gate that has W as one input (and carry_in as the other). Its output should be zN. If not, its output and zN are swapped.\n     * Find the AND gate with inputs xN,yN. Its output is the generate wire.\n     * Find the AND gate with W and carry_in as inputs. Its output is the propagate wire.\n     * Find the OR gate with generate and propagate as inputs. Its output is the carry_out for the next bit.\n   - For the last bit: the carry should equal z(NN+1). If not, they are swapped.\n   \n   When a swap is detected, fix it in place (swap the out fields of the two affected gates) and record both wire names. This allows subsequent bits to be analyzed correctly.\n\nConstraints:\n- Language: TypeScript with strict mode\n- Module: ES module (use export, not module.exports)\n- Dependencies: stdlib only, no external packages\n- No markdown fences in output, just raw TypeScript code\n- The Gate interface, simulate, and findSwappedWires must all be named exports\n\nOutput ONLY the TypeScript code for src/index.ts. No markdown fences. No explanation.' -o text 2>&1)\necho \"$OUTPUT\"","description":"Delegate implementation to Gemini CLI","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":484,"cache_read_input_tokens":20840,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":484},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b652f3a-f921-4a07-9246-2ee54cf992bd","uuid":"ec7066c3-992d-444c-8579-e00535dab83e"}
